\u00e0stic de Tarragona footballers]]\n[[Category:SD Ponferradina players]]\n[[Category:AD Alcorc\u00f3n footballers]]\n[[Category:RCD Espanyol footballers]]\n[[Category:Liga MX players]]\n[[Category:Club Universidad Nacional footballers]]\n[[Category:Lobos BUAP footballers]]\n[[Category:C.D. Veracruz footballers]]\n[[Category:Cypriot First Division players]]\n[[Category:AEK Larnaca FC players]]\n[[Category:Catalonia international footballers]]\n[[Category:Spanish expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Mexico]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Cyprus]]\n[[Category:Spanish expatriate sportspeople in Mexico]]\n[[Category:Spanish expatriate sportspeople in Cyprus]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Spanish footballer}}\n{{Spanish name|Gonz\u00e1lez|Casanova}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2013}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Abraham Gonz\u00e1lez\n| image =\n| fullname = Abraham Gonz\u00e1lez Casanova\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1985|7|16|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Barcelona]], Spain\n| height = {{convert|1.75|m|ftin|0|abbr=on}}\n| position = [[Midfielder#Central midfielder|Midfielder]]\n| currentclub = [[AEK Larnaca FC|AEK Larnaca]]\n| clubnumber = 6\n| youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = Ferr\u00e1n Martorell\n| youthyears2 = 2002\u20132004 | youthclubs2 = [[Terrassa FC|Terrassa]]\n| years1 = 2004\u20132007 | clubs1 = [[Terrassa FC|Terrassa]] | caps1 = 74 | goals1 = 3\n| years2 = 2007\u20132009 | clubs2 = [[FC Barcelona B|Barcelona B]] | caps2 = 67 | goals2 = 4\n| years3 = 2008\u20132009 | clubs3 = [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] | caps3 = 1 | goals3 = 0\n| years4 = 2009\u20132010 | clubs4 = [[C\u00e1diz CF|C\u00e1diz]] | caps4 = 32 | goals4 = 2\n| years5 = 2010\u20132011 | clubs5 = [[Gimn\u00e0stic de Tarragona|Gimn\u00e0stic]] | caps5 = 4 | goals5 = 0\n| years6 = 2011 | clubs6 = \u2192 [[SD Ponferradina|Ponferradina]] (loan) | caps6 = 17 | goals6 = 0\n| years7 = 2011\u20132013 | clubs7 = [[AD Alcorc\u00f3n|Alcorc\u00f3n]] | caps7 = 68 | goals7 = 2\n| years8 = 2013\u20132016 | clubs8 = [[RCD Espanyol|Espanyol]] | caps8 = 63 | goals8 = 2\n| years9 = 2016\u20132019 | clubs9 = [[Club Universidad Nacional|UNAM]] | caps9 = 67 | goals9 = 6\n| years10 = 2018\u20132019 | clubs10 = \u2192 [[Lobos BUAP|BUAP]] (loan) | caps10 = 34 | goals10 = 0\n| years11 = 2019 | clubs11 = \u2192 [[Tiburones Rojos de Veracruz|Veracruz]] (loan) | caps11 = 13 | goals11 = 0\n| years12 = 2020\u2013 | clubs12 = [[AEK Larnaca FC|AEK Larnaca]] | caps12 =  5 | goals12 = 0\n| totalcaps = | totalgoals = \n| nationalyears1 = 2006 | nationalteam1 = [[Catalonia national football team|Catalonia]] | nationalcaps1 = 1 | nationalgoals1 = 0\n| club-update = 8 March 2020\n| nationalteam-update =\n}}\n\n'''Abraham Gonz\u00e1lez Casanova''' (born 16 July 1985) is a Spanish professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for Cypriot club [[AEK Larnaca FC]] as a [[Midfielder#Central midfielder|central midfielder]].\n\n==Club career==\nBorn in [[Barcelona]], [[Catalonia]], Abraham made his professional debut with local [[Terrassa FC]],<ref>[http://www.324.cat/noticia/70810/altres/El-Terrassa-presenta-els-reforcos-de-David-Valle-i-Abraham-Gonzalez El Terrassa presenta els refor\u00e7os de David Valle i Abraham Gonz\u00e1lez (Terrassa present signings David Valle and Abraham Gonz\u00e1lez)]; [[Televisi\u00f3 de Catalunya]], 19 July 2004 (in Catalan)</ref> appearing in 16 matches during the [[2004\u201305 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n|2004\u201305 season]] in the [[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n|second division]], which ended in relegation.\n\nTwo years later, he was bought by neighbours [[FC Barcelona]], being immediately assigned to its [[FC Barcelona B|reserve side]] which competed in the [[Tercera Divisi\u00f3n|fourth level]]. He made his debut for the first team during the [[Copa del Rey]] tie against [[Benidorm CF]] ([[2008\u201309 Copa del Rey|1\u20130 win]]) on 28 October 2008;<ref>[http://archivo.marca.com/edicion/marca/futbol/copa_del_rey/previaxcronica/es/desarrollo/1179308.html El Bar\u00e7a no se salta el gui\u00f3n (Bar\u00e7a stay par for course)]; [[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]], 28 October 2008 (in Spanish)</ref> in [[2008\u201309 La Liga|the last round]] of [[La Liga]], as ''Bar\u00e7a'' were already champions, he came on as a [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for [[Xavi]] during the 1\u20131 draw at [[Deportivo de La Coru\u00f1a]].<ref>[http://soccernet.espn.go.com/report/_/id/252852?cc=5739 Deportivo La Coru\u00f1a 1\u20131 Barcelona]; [[ESPN FC|ESPN Soccernet]], 30 May 2009</ref>\n\nAbraham was released by Barcelona in the summer of 2009, joining [[C\u00e1diz CF]] as the club had just [[2008\u201309 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B|returned to division two]] after a one-year absence. He appeared regularly for the [[Andalusia]]ns, who were [[2009\u201310 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n|immediately relegated back]].\n\nAbraham signed with [[Gimn\u00e0stic de Tarragona]] for the [[2010\u201311 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n|2010\u201311 campaign]],<ref>[http://www.marca.com/2010/07/17/futbol/equipos/gimnastic/1279376859.html Ra\u00fal Fuster y Abraham Gonz\u00e1lez refuerzan al N\u00e1stic (Ra\u00fal Fuster and Abraham Gonz\u00e1lez strengthen N\u00e1stic)]; Marca, 17 July 2010 (in Spanish)</ref> but failed to impress at his new club. In the following [[transfer window]] he was loaned to fellow league side [[SD Ponferradina]],<ref>[http://www.marca.com/2011/01/28/futbol/equipos/ponferradina/1296238468.html Dos nuevos fichajes para el centro del campo (Two new midfield signings)]; Marca, 28 January 2011 (in Spanish)</ref> eventually suffering another relegation.\n\nOn 15 July 2011, Abraham joined [[AD Alcorc\u00f3n]] also in the second tier.<ref>[http://www.marca.com/2011/07/15/futbol/equipos/alcorcon/1310756175.html Abraham Gonz\u00e1lez se convierte en el cuarto refuerzo del Alcorc\u00f3n (Abraham Gonz\u00e1lez becomes Alcorc\u00f3n's fourth signing)]; Marca, 15 July 2011 (in Spanish)</ref> After two seasons as a starter (both missing promotion in the [[play-offs]]), he moved to [[La Liga]] with [[RCD Espanyol]].<ref>[http://www.goal.com/es/news/21/fichajes/2013/06/19/4059956/el-espanyol-ficha-a-abraham-gonz%C3%A1lez-y-juan-rafael-fuentes El Espanyol ficha a Abraham Gonz\u00e1lez y Juan Rafael Fuentes (Espanyol sign Abraham Gonz\u00e1lez and Juan Rafael Fuentes)]; [[Goal (website)|Goal]], 19 June 2013 (in Spanish)</ref>\n\nAbraham scored his first goal in the [[Spanish football league system|Spanish top flight]] on 27 February 2015, netting the game's only in a home success over [[C\u00f3rdoba CF]].<ref>[http://www.marca.com/eventos/marcador/futbol/2014_15/la-liga/jornada_25/esp_cor/ El Espanyol no descuida la Liga (Espanyol keep an eye on the League)]; Marca, 27 February 2015 (in Spanish)</ref> On 17 June 2016, after three seasons with an average of 21 league appearances, the 30-year-old moved abroad for the first time in his career, signing with [[Club Universidad Nacional]] from the [[Liga MX]] as a [[free agent]].<ref>[http://www.rcdespanyol.com/ca/actualitat/abraham-finalitza-la-seva-etapa-a-lespanyol/_n:3081/ Abraham finalitza la seva etapa a l\u2019Espanyol (Abraham ends Espanyol spell)]; RCD Espanyol, 17 June 2016 (in Catalan)</ref>\n\n==Club statistics==\n{{updated|9 June 2011}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/abraham-gonzalez-casanova/62793/|title=Abraham|publisher=Soccerway|accessdate=2 April 2014}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"2\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[UEFA|Europe]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\" align=center valign=center|[[Terrassa FC|Terrassa]]\n|!colspan=\"2\"|[[2004\u201305 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n|2004\u201305]]\n|16||1||2||1||\u2014||\u2014||18||2\n|-\n|!colspan=\"2\"|[[2005\u201306 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B|2005\u201306]]\n|26||2||1||0||\u2014||\u2014|